WEBVTT

00:00.674 --> 00:03.739
Thank you for downloading or streaming this message from Immanuel Church.

00:04.160 --> 00:08.648
We are one church with multiple locations, and we believe God wants to bless you right where you are.

00:08.688 --> 00:14.799
In a few moments, you're going to hear some practical teaching from God's Word that I believe will be inspiring and relevant to your life.

00:15.560 --> 00:25.458
First, though, if you haven't yet experienced Immanuel Live, we encourage you to go to our website, eclive.org, to check out our service times and locations so that you can experience Immanuel in person

00:25.538 --> 00:26.760
or through our online campus.

00:27.462 --> 00:36.238
If this message blesses you and you'd like to support the ministry financially, again, you can go to eclive.org and click on the giving tab and choose online campus at your campus.

00:36.919 --> 00:41.427
Thanks again for joining us today, and we hope this message will be an encouragement to you on your spiritual journey.

00:44.653 --> 00:45.535
Well, good morning, church.

00:46.857 --> 00:48.220
Merry Christmas to everyone.

00:48.260 --> 00:49.522
How's everybody feeling today?

00:54.114 --> 00:57.743
I've got my Christmas socks on here today, a little Santa Claus, a little snowflakes.

00:57.783 --> 00:58.665
I'm feeling pretty good.

00:59.407 --> 01:01.893
This is the fifth time that I'm going to be giving this talk.

01:02.074 --> 01:07.186
So if I repeat myself or stutter a little bit, it's because I am repeating myself.

01:07.554 --> 01:15.410
But I do want to welcome everyone right now watching at all of our campuses, Garfield Park, Banta, Franklin, Greenwood, everyone in our overflow out there.

01:15.430 --> 01:16.653
Can we say hi to the overflow out there?

01:16.673 --> 01:17.755
Hi guys, I see you.

01:17.795 --> 01:22.084
Everyone watching online right now and also at our micro sites.

01:22.485 --> 01:25.170
We just want to give it up for everyone watching right now.

01:28.962 --> 01:33.114
This is the last installment of a three week series called Tis the Season.

01:33.215 --> 01:34.258
It's our Christmas series.

01:34.659 --> 01:43.826
We love Christmas here at Emmanuel, and we've been talking about this idea of that Christmas is all about joy and peace, and it's actually right in the Christmas story.

01:44.002 --> 01:53.542
If you just heard it a few moments ago at your campus read by the worship leaders that, you know, Mary and Joseph go down to Bethlehem to be counted in the sense, in the census, her water breaks.

01:53.582 --> 01:54.785
There's no room in the end.

01:54.805 --> 01:58.132
So they wrap up the baby, you know, and they put him in the manger.

01:58.493 --> 01:59.695
Well, well, that's all happening.

01:59.715 --> 02:02.862
There's some shepherds out in the field guarding their sheep, right?

02:02.882 --> 02:04.786
And all of a sudden an angel shows up.

02:05.026 --> 02:11.014
And his brilliance is, he's so bright that they're frightened and they're terrified.

02:11.054 --> 02:14.699
And so in verse 14, I'm sorry, in verse 10 of Luke chapter two, it says this.

02:15.380 --> 02:19.246
They were terrified, but the angel reassured them saying, don't be afraid.

02:20.267 --> 02:25.775
I bring you good news that will bring great, say with me, joy to all people.

02:25.815 --> 02:28.338
Like Christmas, it's about joy.

02:28.770 --> 02:32.233
Not long after that, a whole host of angels joined this one angel.

02:32.554 --> 02:36.818
And together in verse 14, this is what they say, glory to God in the highest heaven.

02:37.538 --> 02:42.263
And say with me, peace on earth with whom God is pleased.

02:42.283 --> 02:45.426
Like Christmas is about joy and peace.

02:45.526 --> 02:49.850
And for many of us, that's pretty easy to experience around this time of the year.

02:50.690 --> 02:52.012
We love Christmas time.

02:52.052 --> 02:55.175
It's filled with family time, time off from work.

02:55.195 --> 02:57.197
How many of you are getting time off from work?

02:57.217 --> 02:58.738
Yeah, it's exciting.

02:59.042 --> 03:00.945
Some of you have to work.

03:00.985 --> 03:03.248
That's sad, but a lot of us don't.

03:04.550 --> 03:07.335
But there's, you know, it's a beautiful time.

03:07.355 --> 03:17.149
There's music and there's decorations and there's gift sharing and receiving and, you know, there's fun food and there's special drinks at Starbucks.

03:17.450 --> 03:18.271
It's just so much.

03:19.012 --> 03:24.080
And we've even gotten some snow here recently here in Greenwood, locally here in Greenwood.

03:24.100 --> 03:28.146
If you're watching online some other part of the country, maybe you don't have snow, but we have some here.

03:28.226 --> 03:30.509
And that's a fun time for our dogs, isn't it?

03:30.869 --> 03:32.170
Anybody have a dog that loves the snow?

03:32.891 --> 03:33.252
We do.

03:33.472 --> 03:34.053
We just got one.

03:34.073 --> 03:35.294
We have a golden doodle.

03:35.434 --> 03:36.015
He's a puppy.

03:36.035 --> 03:38.538
He's 50 pounds, but he's still a puffy puppy.

03:39.098 --> 03:39.999
Here's a picture of our guy.

03:40.019 --> 03:40.840
His name is Toby.

03:41.241 --> 03:42.462
He loves the snow.

03:42.502 --> 03:47.888
He went out the other day and he just shoved his face in it and got all matted in his beard and he got the whole house wet.

03:47.908 --> 03:51.092
But, you know, Christmas time and dogs, you know, it's a good time of the year.

03:51.272 --> 03:51.773
Anybody else?

03:52.053 --> 03:52.554
Dog lovers?

03:53.875 --> 03:54.996
Cats not so much, right?

03:55.056 --> 03:55.197
No.

03:55.497 --> 03:56.498
They don't like the snow.

03:58.370 --> 04:06.361
It's easy for some of us to have, you know, literally experience the most wonderful time of the year, that it's Christmas time.

04:06.381 --> 04:09.585
And of course, Jesus is the baby and that helps us to find joy and peace.

04:10.767 --> 04:16.134
But then there's some others of us that it's not so easy to experience joy and peace.

04:16.215 --> 04:17.556
It's a little bit more challenging.

04:17.636 --> 04:20.801
The hustle and the bustle and the busyness and the traffic.

04:20.821 --> 04:21.682
Oh, the traffic.

04:21.922 --> 04:24.505
This week, it's just been two o'clock in the afternoon, gridlock.

04:25.626 --> 04:27.588
It's like, how come these people aren't at work?

04:29.029 --> 04:29.870
Where's their bossa?

04:30.210 --> 04:30.731
Call somebody.

04:30.751 --> 04:31.252
Anyway.

04:33.854 --> 04:34.455
It's hectic.

04:34.495 --> 04:35.055
It's tense.

04:35.075 --> 04:36.337
There's a lot of expectations.

04:36.357 --> 04:37.618
You got to go different places.

04:38.579 --> 04:40.321
You got to wrap gifts, buy gifts.

04:40.421 --> 04:41.022
It's stressful.

04:41.042 --> 04:44.385
The average couple has seven arguments over the Christmas break.

04:44.405 --> 04:45.646
I mean, what does that say right there?

04:46.267 --> 04:47.068
Stress is up.

04:47.088 --> 04:47.989
Where are we going to spend time?

04:48.009 --> 04:49.330
We're spending extra money.

04:49.570 --> 04:54.896
Then there's family tensions that we have to deal with that we normally don't have to deal with, but Christmas time, everybody gets together.

04:54.916 --> 04:58.301
And we talked about that last week, how to have peace with the family.

04:58.321 --> 05:01.104
You know, if you missed that, you might wanna check that out.

05:01.124 --> 05:03.447
If you got some problems with your family, everybody does.

05:04.768 --> 05:09.414
And then there's another group of us that struggle to find joy and peace during Christmas because of something else.

05:10.355 --> 05:12.037
And we're gonna call that something else today.

05:12.077 --> 05:13.599
We're gonna call it the empty chair.

05:15.141 --> 05:16.082
The empty chair.

05:17.186 --> 05:20.871
Because this Christmas, there's gonna be someone in your house that's missing.

05:22.653 --> 05:30.744
And maybe there's a person missing this year because there's been a divorce, and now that person's not gonna be with you, a mother, a father.

05:32.566 --> 05:41.938
Maybe there's somebody gonna be in the, maybe there's an empty chair in your house today because someone's been deployed in the military, they're overseas serving our country somewhere, and so they're absent.

05:43.234 --> 05:44.275
Maybe it's something worse.

05:44.315 --> 05:45.477
Maybe it's something like prison.

05:45.517 --> 05:49.321
They've broken the law and now they're not with you because they're in prison.

05:50.282 --> 05:59.393
Maybe it's because there's a family fight or some sort of addiction that has broken the family up and now that person is no longer with you and there's just tension in the family.

06:00.855 --> 06:02.377
Maybe it's because someone's passed away.

06:04.019 --> 06:08.064
They're just not with you anymore because God took them.

06:09.506 --> 06:13.170
For whatever reason, this Christmas is, there's an empty chair.

06:13.506 --> 06:19.352
And for some of you, there's been an empty chair for two years, three years, four years, five years, even longer.

06:19.452 --> 06:21.675
And so for you, Christmas is a tougher time.

06:23.637 --> 06:27.721
Because it's a time where you're reminded that the person you love is no longer with you.

06:28.222 --> 06:31.345
Nancy Guthrie is a woman who's familiar with loss.

06:31.626 --> 06:34.349
She lost two children to a very rare disease.

06:36.010 --> 06:38.813
And she wrote a book about it when your family loses a loved one.

06:38.833 --> 06:43.058
And she actually wrote a whole series of content called griefshare.

06:43.138 --> 06:46.041
that many churches take their people through.

06:46.081 --> 06:47.863
We actually do it here at the church as well.

06:49.025 --> 06:51.888
In her book, this is what she says to families that have lost loved ones.

06:52.849 --> 06:59.917
For families who have recently lost someone they loved, the holidays can seem more like something to survive rather than to enjoy.

06:59.957 --> 07:11.410
The traditions and the events that can add so much joy and meaning to the season are punctuated with painful, repeated reminders of the loss.

07:12.354 --> 07:20.967
She says this, many of us wish we could find a quiet place to hide until January 2nd.

07:20.987 --> 07:24.212
Some of you are like, man, this is getting real depressing.

07:25.334 --> 07:29.741
Like I thought we'd come to church for Christmas and it'd be fun and encouraging and happy time.

07:29.801 --> 07:31.524
Why is he talking about this right now?

07:31.804 --> 07:34.629
And here's why we're talking about it because it's real.

07:36.131 --> 07:40.658
I could list off the top of my head five families that I personally know

07:40.802 --> 07:44.426
that are going through this Christmas for the first time with an empty chair.

07:44.566 --> 07:45.046
It's real.

07:47.188 --> 07:48.169
There's someone missing.

07:48.990 --> 07:51.313
And because there's someone missing, it's very hard.

07:52.274 --> 08:07.709
And even if you don't have an empty chair this Christmas, even if everyone is going to be around the tree for you or around the dinner table for you and everyone's healthy and everyone's present, you know, I guarantee you know someone very close to you that is experiencing the empty chair.

08:07.769 --> 08:08.370
Yes or no?

08:09.090 --> 08:23.911
So maybe today you hear something that is not directly for you, maybe it'll be for you in the future, but it's not directly for you right now, but it's for you to pass on to someone else who is having a tough time experiencing joy and peace because they are experiencing the empty chair.

08:25.654 --> 08:28.097
Think beyond yourself just for a few moments.

08:28.117 --> 08:28.939
Who is that person?

08:29.580 --> 08:32.984
And they're not here, but they need to hear what I'm gonna say today.

08:34.487 --> 08:36.850
Why is it so hard for these folks

08:37.602 --> 08:43.108
I mean, obviously the obvious answer is the person they love is not physically present, okay?

08:43.149 --> 08:44.170
That's the obvious answer.

08:44.190 --> 08:49.896
But as I've talked to some of my friends who are going through this, it goes beyond that.

08:50.277 --> 08:52.399
It's not just that the person is physically not there.

08:52.419 --> 08:58.567
It's also the reality that things are just not the same.

09:00.889 --> 09:01.991
There's laughter missing.

09:04.153 --> 09:04.914
This person

09:06.338 --> 09:07.520
brought hugs and kisses.

09:07.980 --> 09:09.663
Those are missing.

09:09.683 --> 09:11.225
This person had conversations.

09:11.265 --> 09:12.668
The conversations are missing.

09:14.230 --> 09:15.332
This person baked the cookies.

09:15.712 --> 09:17.635
Now, this person did the wrapping.

09:17.655 --> 09:21.942
This person did the, now that, now the cooking, someone else has to jump in.

09:23.704 --> 09:28.892
This person did the shoveling and they cleared off the driveway and now someone else has to.

09:29.273 --> 09:32.197
Things are just not the same.

09:33.459 --> 09:35.282
And that's why the pain runs so deep.

09:35.906 --> 09:39.490
and the normal traditions that brought joy and happiness and the things that we did together.

09:39.791 --> 09:42.294
Now they're just reminders of our loss.

09:44.236 --> 09:47.941
And so we struggle because things are just not the same.

09:47.981 --> 09:49.283
Here's the question I want to ask today.

09:49.663 --> 09:55.050
Is it possible for those of us who are experiencing the empty chair or your friends who are experiencing the empty chair?

09:55.290 --> 10:03.720
Is it possible for them, for you to have joy and peace, even in the midst of loss, missing that love?

10:03.841 --> 10:05.042
I would argue yes.

10:05.218 --> 10:05.639
there is.

10:05.999 --> 10:07.562
I'm going to give you a couple of ideas here.

10:07.602 --> 10:09.264
Grab a pen, jot these down.

10:09.305 --> 10:15.114
I believe they can be extraordinarily helpful for you today or for someone that you know.

10:15.134 --> 10:23.307
How can you and I experience joy and peace when we are going through the holidays without someone we love?

10:23.327 --> 10:25.170
Number one, you have to give yourself a pass.

10:25.538 --> 10:26.880
You have to give yourself a pass.

10:26.900 --> 10:27.640
What do I mean by that?

10:27.680 --> 10:32.726
What I mean is you got to let yourself off the hook, you got to give yourself some grace, you got to release the expectations.

10:32.766 --> 10:35.790
Listen, every single family has expectations over the holidays.

10:36.150 --> 10:42.538
We go here, we go to grandma's house on 24th, we wrap gifts on the 22nd, we make cookies on this day, and we just do, we do all these things.

10:42.558 --> 10:53.170
Your family has expectations, my family has expectations, and maybe this year, because you're going through the empty chair situation, you just give yourself a break and you let yourself miss.

10:54.562 --> 10:59.108
You say, I'm not going to continue to grind so that I make everybody happy and nobody gets upset with me.

10:59.168 --> 11:00.811
No, I'm just going to give myself a break.

11:01.131 --> 11:02.813
I'm going to ask myself this question.

11:03.715 --> 11:06.538
What will allow me to experience joy and peace?

11:06.699 --> 11:09.302
What will allow you to experience joy and peace?

11:10.444 --> 11:14.930
Do not feel obligated to meet everyone's expectations during Christmas time.

11:15.650 --> 11:19.896
Well, I always get everyone a gift, and I wrap it, and I give it out to release the expectation.

11:19.916 --> 11:21.298
Well, I always write Christmas cards.

11:21.739 --> 11:23.862
I always make the banana bread.

11:24.362 --> 11:25.484
I always do these things.

11:25.504 --> 11:27.347
Release yourself from the expectations.

11:28.548 --> 11:38.563
I had a friend who lost her husband recently, and I overheard that she was apologizing to someone because she hadn't written her Christmas cards yet.

11:40.345 --> 11:40.946
It's like, wait a second.

11:41.250 --> 11:42.231
You get a pass.

11:42.631 --> 11:44.073
No Christmas cards this year.

11:44.513 --> 11:45.074
It's okay.

11:45.334 --> 11:48.637
In fact, you never have to do Christmas cards again for the rest of your life.

11:48.657 --> 11:49.458
No Christmas cards.

11:49.899 --> 11:51.961
You are missing your husband.

11:52.541 --> 11:54.263
You get a pass.

11:55.124 --> 11:57.666
A lot of the expectations we put on ourselves, yes?

11:58.507 --> 11:58.948
Yes or no?

11:59.388 --> 12:01.130
Well, I've always done this and I gotta do.

12:01.570 --> 12:02.792
Wait a second, time out.

12:02.812 --> 12:07.156
If you continue to grind through and just try to meet the expectations, your soul's not gonna heal.

12:07.556 --> 12:09.298
You're not gonna experience joy and peace.

12:10.498 --> 12:17.473
And by the way, if you're the person who's supporting this person right here, you have to give them a pass and give it ahead of time.

12:17.493 --> 12:24.469
Say this year, if you don't want to come to the dinner, if you want to do the exchange of the presents, if you don't want to make the cookies, you don't have to.

12:24.789 --> 12:26.112
How can we serve you?

12:27.295 --> 12:29.219
Listen to what Paul said in 1 Corinthians 13.

12:29.259 --> 12:30.642
He said, love is patient.

12:31.362 --> 12:36.169
That's what love is the first thing he describes, and he says love is a bunch of things, but the first thing is patient.

12:36.229 --> 12:37.070
Love is patient.

12:37.090 --> 12:38.092
It means long-suffering.

12:38.573 --> 12:42.739
It means whatever you need to do this Christmas to heal, we will do that.

12:42.839 --> 12:45.202
You're the person experiencing the empty chair.

12:45.723 --> 12:53.074
How can we support you out of friend recently who told me that 10 years ago she lost her brother right before her 30th birthday?

12:55.458 --> 13:01.324
And she is the type of person who typically loves gifts and loves parties and the more the better.

13:01.505 --> 13:02.866
I mean, that's the type of person this is.

13:03.827 --> 13:12.977
But she was so sad over the loss of her brother that she went to her family and she said, hey, I don't really want a party and I don't want presents and I don't want a big deal made over this.

13:13.037 --> 13:18.863
I'm grieving over the loss of my brother and so please don't do that.

13:18.943 --> 13:25.170
Well, her family decided not only to throw her a party but to throw her a surprise birthday party for her 30th birthday.

13:27.426 --> 13:29.690
You know what my friend told me this week as I was questioning?

13:29.710 --> 13:31.232
Because I've never been through something like that.

13:31.292 --> 13:32.254
My brothers are still alive.

13:34.938 --> 13:40.508
She said, even now as I look back at the pictures of the party, I cuss in my head.

13:42.371 --> 13:43.953
This is a Christian lady.

13:43.973 --> 13:47.479
This is a Christian lady who works on our staff.

13:49.643 --> 13:50.404
You shouldn't cuss.

13:50.484 --> 13:52.587
Now thankfully she doesn't cuss out loud, but she just cusses.

13:52.628 --> 13:54.130
She keeps it in her head.

13:54.210 --> 13:59.879
But there are no fond memories of that party because that's not what she needed at that time.

14:00.340 --> 14:05.829
See, if you're trying to support someone going through this situation right here, you don't give them what you think they need.

14:05.889 --> 14:08.192
You don't even give them what you would need yourself.

14:08.252 --> 14:11.197
You give them what they would need, which is just space.

14:12.579 --> 14:13.741
Release the expectations.

14:13.801 --> 14:14.522
We're not going to do it.

14:15.163 --> 14:16.546
If you don't want to do it, we're not going to do it.

14:16.566 --> 14:18.569
We're going to give you a pass.

14:18.589 --> 14:19.250
Yes or no?

14:19.554 --> 14:23.279
Number one, give yourself a pass, give people a pass.

14:23.299 --> 14:25.642
Number two, create a new or start a new tradition.

14:26.143 --> 14:36.797
Listen, traditions, the whole purpose behind a tradition, whether it's singing carols or making cookies or whatever it is that you do as a family, is to bring joy and happiness around this time of the year.

14:38.119 --> 14:40.402
Well, if you continue to do those traditions,

14:40.546 --> 14:44.951
And all those traditions do is remind you of the person who's missing.

14:45.331 --> 14:48.235
What you're going to do is create sorrow over and over.

14:48.495 --> 14:51.378
You're going to rip the band-aid off over and over.

14:51.418 --> 15:01.790
So as I've researched this and studied people who've lost family members and who don't have people with them during the holidays, what they say is to start a new tradition.

15:01.850 --> 15:06.355
Do something different that you've never done with this person.

15:07.176 --> 15:09.298
Not to forget them, not saying that.

15:09.474 --> 15:10.315
They're not saying that.

15:10.435 --> 15:17.806
They're saying to shift the focus and to create a new memory so that you can raise the possibility of joy and peace.

15:18.768 --> 15:19.749
So what am I talking about?

15:19.789 --> 15:21.612
Well, maybe you have a game night.

15:21.632 --> 15:24.556
You do something and you invite the family over and you play Settlers of Catan.

15:24.576 --> 15:25.277
You ever play that game?

15:25.778 --> 15:26.539
Oh, that's a good game.

15:26.559 --> 15:27.040
We play that.

15:27.100 --> 15:36.434
I usually win in my house and listen, my wife beats me, but my kids will probably differ if you ask them, but maybe you have a game night.

15:36.770 --> 15:41.176
Maybe you go serve someone underprivileged at a food bank somewhere.

15:41.997 --> 15:44.100
Maybe you do a movie night on December 24th.

15:44.120 --> 15:44.861
You go see the movies.

15:44.881 --> 15:46.123
There's a new movie out right now.

15:46.183 --> 15:46.823
It's Star Wars.

15:47.124 --> 15:47.785
Have you heard about it?

15:47.805 --> 15:48.466
Anybody see it yet?

15:49.527 --> 15:49.848
Anybody?

15:49.888 --> 15:50.208
Anybody?

15:50.649 --> 15:51.610
I went and saw it the other night.

15:51.730 --> 15:52.892
Who hasn't seen it right now?

15:53.052 --> 15:59.320
Oh, man, there's this one scene where... No, Kylo, Kylo, what's his name?

15:59.340 --> 16:02.625
Kylo, he gets his lightsaber out and he's about to...

16:02.645 --> 16:04.527
I won't give it away, but it's really good.

16:04.547 --> 16:05.048
It's really good.

16:05.168 --> 16:06.610
I've done that before and gotten in trouble.

16:07.874 --> 16:12.119
Maybe you do a movie, maybe you do a Christmas movie tradition, and you start something new.

16:12.460 --> 16:19.368
Again, not to forget your loved one, but to shift the focus away from loss and grieving is something happy and joyful with new people around you.

16:20.710 --> 16:24.274
And maybe for some of you, the old traditions, they actually help you.

16:25.395 --> 16:37.490
And you've gotten through it so far where decorating the tree or the old traditions used to do, making cookies or whatever it is, wrapping presents, they help you to remember this person and you have good emotions, then hey, praise God, do those.

16:38.498 --> 16:41.301
The idea is try to create joy in peace.

16:41.362 --> 16:44.646
Don't try to rip the band-aid over off again and again.

16:45.767 --> 16:47.129
Create some new traditions.

16:47.169 --> 16:49.011
Number three, surround yourself with the right people.

16:49.531 --> 16:50.252
The right people.

16:51.394 --> 16:52.155
Who are the right people?

16:52.195 --> 16:58.302
The right people are the people who will encourage you and support you and build you up and provide comfort for you.

16:58.943 --> 17:07.954
I believe with all my heart that God's strategy or one of God's strategies to help you work through loss or the missing chair or the empty chair is other

17:08.066 --> 17:09.748
people, the right people.

17:09.948 --> 17:10.929
That's God's strategy.

17:11.650 --> 17:14.212
Romans chapter 12, verse 15 says this.

17:14.273 --> 17:16.935
Rejoice with those who rejoice and mourn with those who mourn.

17:17.556 --> 17:20.960
If someone is happy, if someone is excited, then be excited with them.

17:21.180 --> 17:27.026
If someone is sad, if someone is down, if someone is hurting, if someone is missing their loved one, then mourn with them.

17:27.086 --> 17:28.067
Be sad with them.

17:28.227 --> 17:30.229
Meet them where they are.

17:30.369 --> 17:31.671
That's love, isn't it?

17:32.151 --> 17:34.674
Isn't love doing what is best for someone else?

17:36.162 --> 17:37.384
The right people do that.

17:37.464 --> 17:41.269
Nancy Guthrie and her book, when a family loses a loved one, this is what she said.

17:42.050 --> 17:45.895
Choose to be around people you can count on to understand your sorrow.

17:46.136 --> 17:47.658
That simply means to empathize.

17:47.678 --> 17:49.020
Someone who gets your pain.

17:49.841 --> 17:51.583
Surround yourself with these type of people.

17:51.663 --> 17:56.590
People who offer you emotional and spiritual support that you need to get through the holiday season.

17:57.211 --> 17:58.493
The right people do that.

17:59.494 --> 18:00.796
