19:27.824 --> 19:29.426
You have to cling to God for comfort.

19:30.242 --> 19:31.704
You have to cling to God for comfort.

19:31.744 --> 19:32.926
This is the most important one.

19:35.329 --> 19:36.130
What do I mean by that?

19:36.231 --> 19:43.281
Well, suffering, pain, loss always puts in front of us a choice.

19:44.703 --> 19:46.485
It always creates an option for us.

19:47.827 --> 19:53.756
You see, when it comes to loss or pain or suffering, we have this desire to get relief.

19:53.916 --> 19:55.619
All we want is the pain to be eased.

19:56.179 --> 19:58.002
And so what we'll do is we'll turn to food,

19:58.914 --> 20:02.520
Many of us, because it's easy, it's cheap, it's affordable, it's right in the refrigerator.

20:03.661 --> 20:06.606
And so we don't just gain a little weight because there's a lot of food around the holidays.

20:06.666 --> 20:12.034
We gain some weight because we're looking for relief for the situation.

20:13.156 --> 20:13.957
So we'll turn to food.

20:14.198 --> 20:20.567
Some of us will turn to alcohol because for in a short amount of time, you know, we can tend to forget our problems and sort of get some relief.

20:20.627 --> 20:22.290
We know that doesn't work long term.

20:23.746 --> 20:26.870
Some of us will turn to pills or drugs to get some relief from the pain.

20:26.890 --> 20:28.893
Some of us will turn to another relationship.

20:28.913 --> 20:32.257
And so we'll get online and we'll try to connect with somebody or hook up with somebody.

20:32.898 --> 20:36.863
Or some of us will double down and put more of our hearts into work and become workaholic.

20:36.923 --> 20:37.124
Why?

20:37.344 --> 20:38.786
Because we're looking for relief.

20:39.587 --> 20:41.069
We want the pain to be eased.

20:42.891 --> 20:43.752
Some of us will sleep.

20:43.812 --> 20:44.513
We'll just go to bed.

20:44.733 --> 20:46.856
We're struggling so much.

20:46.876 --> 20:47.838
It's like, I can't even cope.

20:47.858 --> 20:48.659
I'm just going to go to bed.

20:48.679 --> 20:49.380
I'm just going to sleep.

20:49.440 --> 20:51.282
And we know long term that doesn't work.

20:52.994 --> 20:55.717
Suffering always presents us with an option.

20:55.737 --> 20:59.921
We're gonna choose one of those options or we're gonna choose God.

21:00.882 --> 21:03.024
Listen to what the Apostle Paul said in 2 Corinthians.

21:03.905 --> 21:07.830
God is our merciful father and the source of all of our state with me.

21:08.450 --> 21:10.452
Comfort.

21:10.472 --> 21:12.294
Periclesitos, that's the Greek word.

21:13.095 --> 21:13.976
Comfort.

21:13.996 --> 21:15.157
What does it mean to be comforted?

21:16.739 --> 21:19.762
It means to have your, the load lightened.

21:20.290 --> 21:20.510
Right?

21:20.811 --> 21:25.016
It means for someone to come alongside and help you carry the emotional pain.

21:25.256 --> 21:28.480
It means for someone to come alongside of you and make it not so hard, right?

21:29.201 --> 21:30.823
Isn't that what it means to be comforted?

21:31.124 --> 21:33.587
God is the source of all comforts.

21:33.907 --> 21:43.459
And you and I have to make a choice instead of turning to sleep or pills or food or more work or whatever, we have to turn to God for that comfort.

21:43.579 --> 21:44.380
Paraclitos.

21:44.741 --> 21:48.465
And then Paul says, here's why God wants to comfort you.

21:48.586 --> 21:48.946
Listen.

21:49.538 --> 21:55.204
He comforts us in all of our troubles and all of our pain so that we can stay with me.

21:55.845 --> 21:57.026
Comfort others.

21:57.707 --> 22:04.754
Didn't I say a few moments ago that God's plan and God's strategy for your healing and your support is another person, the right person?

22:04.814 --> 22:07.918
How does God comfort us?

22:09.319 --> 22:10.180
Gives us a person.

22:11.602 --> 22:15.506
Are you, a me, who has received comfort

22:16.354 --> 22:16.975
from God.

22:17.255 --> 22:21.319
Suffering pain loss always presents us with an option.

22:21.339 --> 22:23.100
Where will we turn for relief?

22:23.841 --> 22:27.104
I love what Billy Graham said when it comes to suffering.

22:27.164 --> 22:32.029
Suffering is part of the human condition and it comes to every single one of us.

22:33.410 --> 22:41.317
The key is how we react to it, either turning away from God in anger and bitterness or growing closer to Him in trust and confidence.

22:41.337 --> 22:43.239
The choice is yours.

22:44.160 --> 22:46.322
God says, I am the source of all comfort.

22:47.394 --> 22:52.102
right before Jesus went back to heaven, he said, guys, I'm leaving, but I'm not gonna leave you as orphans.

22:52.222 --> 22:57.251
I'm gonna send you the comforter, the pericletos, the Holy Spirit.

22:57.832 --> 22:58.953
What's his job?

22:59.134 --> 23:06.446
Yes, to guide us into all truth, yes, to convict us of sin, but to come inside of us, to dwell within us, to be our comforter.

23:08.089 --> 23:09.571
