26:06.530 --> 26:11.457
exchange the empty chair for the presence of God.

26:12.218 --> 26:12.839
Will you pray with me?

26:16.765 --> 26:23.274
Precious Father, merciful Father, you are the source of all comfort.

26:25.097 --> 26:26.058
And you comfort us.

26:27.440 --> 26:34.450
You give us what we need to ease the pain for ourselves, yes, but also

26:35.202 --> 26:36.824
that we might extend comfort to others.

26:39.126 --> 26:40.987
Father, thank you for taking the initiative.

26:43.150 --> 27:04.850
When we were doing our own thing, chasing our own desires, when we had our backs turned on, turned from you, you sent Christ into this world, born of a virgin, that Christmas morning, to live his life and eventually give his life

27:04.930 --> 27:19.827
on a cross so that we can be reconciled to you, so that we can live with you, so that we can receive joy and peace and comfort in our pain, in our loss.

27:22.189 --> 27:24.472
Thank you for the gift of Christmas.

27:25.793 --> 27:33.682
Help specifically help those this Christmas season who are experiencing the empty chair.

27:33.922 --> 27:38.568
Maybe for the first time, maybe for the fifth time, maybe the tenth time it still hurts.

27:39.068 --> 27:41.471
I pray that you'd be with them like you've never been with them before.

27:43.394 --> 27:49.021
That you would wrap your arms around them and comfort them like they have never been comforted before.

27:49.061 --> 27:54.027
